  "prompt": "I am losing confidence and self esteem. Can anyone help me?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry to hear that you're feeling this way, but I want you to know that you're not alone, and there are steps you can take to rebuild your confidence and self-esteem. Here are some suggestions:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Practice Self-Compassion**\n   - Be kind to yourself. Treat yourself as you would a close friend who is struggling.\n   - Acknowledge your feelings without judgment\u2014it\u2019s okay to feel this way.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Challenge Negative Thoughts**\n   - Pay attention to your inner dialogue. Are you being overly critical of yourself?\n   - Replace negative thoughts with more balanced, realistic ones. For example, instead of saying, \u201cI\u2019m not good enough,\u201d try, \u201cI\u2019m doing my best, and that\u2019s enough.\u201d\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Set Small, Achievable Goals**\n   - Accomplishing small tasks can help you feel more capable and confident.\n   - Celebrate your progress, no matter how small it seems.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Focus on Your Strengths**\n   - Write down things you\u2019re good at or things you\u2019ve accomplished in the past.\n   - Remind yourself of your unique qualities and what makes you special.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Surround Yourself with Supportive People**\n   - Spend time with people who uplift and encourage you.\n   - Share how you\u2019re feeling with someone you trust\u2014they may offer valuable perspective.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Take Care of Your Body**\n   - Exercise, eat well, and get enough sleep. Physical health can have a big impact on how you feel mentally.\n   - Even a short walk or stretching can help boost your mood.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Practice Gratitude**\n   - Write down three things you\u2019re grateful for each day. This can shift your focus to the positive aspects of your life.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Learn Something New**\n   - Trying a new hobby or skill can help you feel accomplished and boost your self-esteem.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Seek Professional Help**\n   - If your feelings persist or feel overwhelming, consider talking to a therapist or counselor. They can help you work through these emotions and develop healthy coping strategies.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Be Patient with Yourself**\n   - Building confidence and self-esteem takes time. It\u2019s okay to have ups and downs along the way.\n\n---\n\nRemember, you are worthy and capable, even if it doesn\u2019t feel that way right now. Taking small steps to care for yourself can make a big difference. If you\u2019d like more specific advice or just need someone to talk to, feel free to share more about your situation. You\u2019ve got this! \ud83c\udf1f",
  "temperature": 1.0,
